@startuml
title Order Management & Status Flow

actor User
participant "UI: Orders Tab" as UI
participant "UI: Create Order" as Creator
participant "API / Backend" as API
participant "Database" as DB

== Creating an Order (With Customer Logic) ==
User -> UI: Click "Create Order"
UI -> Creator: Open Order Creation Page

== Customer Lookup ==
User -> Creator: Type in Omni-Search (Name/Phone/Email/Address)
Creator -> API: Search Customers
API -> DB: Query Customer Table
DB --> API: Return Matches
API --> Creator: Display Results Dropdown
User -> Creator: Select Existing Customer (Auto-fills form) OR Enter New Details

== Order Submission ==
User -> Creator: Select Product(s) & Set Quantities
User -> Creator: Click "Submit Order"

Creator -> API: Post Order & Customer Data
API -> API: Sanitize Phone Number
API -> DB: Check if Phone Number exists

alt New Customer (Phone Number not found)
    API -> DB: Create New Customer Record
    DB --> API: Return New Customer ID
else Existing Customer
    API -> DB: Update Existing Customer Details (if changed)
    DB --> API: Return Existing Customer ID
end

API -> DB: Save Order Items tied to Customer ID (Status: Pending)
DB --> API: Return Success (Order ID)
API --> Creator: Order Created Notification
Creator --> UI: Redirect back to Orders List

== Managing Orders & Statuses ==
User -> UI: View Orders List
UI -> API: Fetch Orders Data
API -> DB: Query Orders
DB --> API: Return Orders
API --> UI: Render Orders (Preview Info & Current Status)

User -> UI: Filter List by Status (e.g., "Pending")
UI -> UI: Display matching orders

User -> UI: Select Order & Change Status (e.g., Pending -> Making)
UI -> API: Update Order Status Request (OrderID, NewStatus)
API -> DB: Update Status Column in Database
DB --> API: Success
API --> UI: Update Status Badge on UI

== Printing Labels (Single Order) ==
User -> UI: View Order Details
UI -> UI: Display List of Label Templates
User -> UI: Click "Print" on a specific Template

UI -> API: Fetch Template & Global Data Mappings
API --> UI: Return Template Details
UI -> API: Fetch Order & Product Data
API --> UI: Return Data
UI -> UI: (Angular Service) Inject Data into Template Variables
UI -> UI: (Angular Service) Render Final Label to Print Window

UI -> User: Trigger Browser Print (window.print())

== Batch Printing (From Dashboard) ==
User -> UI: Filter Orders (e.g., Status = Packaging)
User -> UI: Check "Select All" (Selects multiple orders)
UI -> UI: Unlock/Enable Dashboard Print Buttons
User -> UI: Click "Print" on a specific Template

UI -> API: Fetch Template & Global Data Mappings
API --> UI: Return Template Details
UI -> API: Fetch Data for ALL selected Orders
API --> UI: Return Array of Orders
UI -> UI: (Angular Service) Loop & Inject Data for each Order/Product
UI -> UI: (Angular Service) Render Multi-Page/Continuous Label Layout

UI -> User: Trigger Browser Print (window.print())

@enduml
